Go check pets out in Lower Guk versus Skyfire and you'll see what I mean.<br>
Mobs just got boosted to hell. velious being the most digusting example, light blue giants that give the epic a hell of a smacking.<br>
<br>
Several problems here:<br>
1) Hyper inflation of mobs, often in ridiculous ways (gimme a break Frost giants should have  ZERO resist to fire!)<br>
2) If pets were made to solo blue mobs to 60...hm wouldnt that be OVERPOWERING? it would be you know, it would mean they could take most melee classes apart, and that is NOT fair. Whats the freaking point of playing a melee then, eh?<br>
3) Pets werent  given enough improvements, balanced with mob and melee upgrades, hopefully this is getting addressed.<br>
4) Damage casters trade defences for offence, speed of set up and durability. Ergo, wizzies mages and necros should have BIG damage out put, but to what extent and how much more than say a warrior?<br>
Me, I'd like to see an AA skill, special spell or whatever that summons a lvl 60 absolute SON OF A B*TCH pet for those special occasions, I see mages in the fantasy sense, they should do jaw dropping stuff now and then, but that's not for every day in Seb etc.<br>
<br>
And Feyia69, I've soloed the Dino with one epic pet quite well thank you, for several hours. How? Dead simple, Nuke, heal pet, nuke, heal pet, nuke...guess what, it works. Then go sit and rod/med/heal back up. Druids take 15 mins or so to kill him, I take about 2 and use 3 -4 bubs mana. necros are best at because they have Fear *shrug*. Dino has 10-15khp, wizards dont like fighting him cause hes a massive manasink, think about it. Shammies are incredibly pwoerful at 60 with Torpor and slow (dino has zip for resists). Rangers can slow him with epic and heal selves.<br>
Chain casting is awesomely powerful, just damn tricky if you have a dial up connection.<br>
<br>
Four pet thing is an Absor myth, ask any mage who saw the Pet Army bug in action, or if you've done raids with mass pets. When NPCs have  4+ attacking you SEE the 5th+ mobs leaving to attack other targets.<br>
<br>
<br>
Redorious<br>
