<br>
No, then we'd be fighting non-stop. Let pet fight mob to death, kill pet, kill mob for full exp, resummon pet. Looking at around 500 mana to spend. With the length of fight, most would be medded up. Not saying that would be *over*powered persay, but it would be a big jump.<br>
<br>
Magicians have the *potential* to be very powerful. They have a few problems though that they can't overcome on their own. We have HUGE damage output (on non-raidlevel mobs), try casting Sirroco/Manastorm back to back. Unless mass-resists, the mob drops like a brick.<br>
<br>
As much as I am a fan of soloing, Im more of a fan of doing things the most efficient way possible (read most exp in least time). From my experience, this is done by duo'ing.<br>
<br>
Mage/Bard in ME, fighting aliens, while a wizard quad kites next to me. I get full exp because 2 flames + 1 SoS = just under half the mobs life (with no casting fury). Adding bard damage means we get full exp, not to mention high frequency of double bolts.<br>
<br>
By the time the wizard has *set up* his quad, Ive usually killed 2-4 aliens. Another 2 or so while he is quading. And then many more while he is medding up all the mana it took him. Every now and then dont nuke for full exp so I can gain some mana back, but usually can regen most of the mana used in the time to kill 2 mobs pulled and pull 2 more (can be long pulls).<br>
<br>
Average exp/hour, bit over a blue in 58 for the bard, and just under a yellow aa for the mage. Once I get more FT and Spell Fury 3, Im guessing this will bump it above 1 yell/hour.<br>
<br>
And this isn't with massive amounts of AA. KEI, TPP, Spell Mastery 2, 1FT item, 1FT from AA.<br>
<br>
And no Boots of Bladecalling or Shield of Auras.<br>
<br>
-Valherji-<br>
